CHAPTER..........
AN ACT relating to governmental financial administration;
establishing conditions of the acceptance of an appropriation
under certain circumstances; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
Existing law establishes various provisions relating to state financing and the
process of appropriation. (NRS 353.150-353.246) This bill requires an entity, as a
condition of the acceptance of an appropriation of state money, to agree to comply
with certain civil rights or employment laws that are applicable to the entity.
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
Section 1. Chapter 353 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
thereto a new section to read as follows:
1. As a condition of the acceptance of an appropriation of
state money, an entity must agree to comply with any civil rights or
employment laws applicable to the entity, including, without
limitation, such laws that contain protections against retaliation
for employees who seek to enforce, administer or otherwise
promote compliance with the law.
2. The acceptance of state money by an entity is deemed
the agreement by the entity to the conditions prescribed by
subsection 1.
3. As used in this section:
(a) “Civil rights or employment laws” means any state or
federal law which prohibits discrimination because of race, creed,
color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or
expression, age or disability. The term includes, without
limitation:
(1) Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, 42 U.S.C. §§
2000e et seq.;
(2) The Age Discrimination in Employment Act of 1967, 29
U.S.C. §§ 621-634;
(3) The Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, 42 U.S.C.
§§ 12101 et seq.; and
(4) NRS 613.310 to 613.4383, inclusive.
